1 Depending on Administrative Agent’s systems, the following alternative language may be appropriate: “From 

and after the Effective Date, the Administrative Agent shall make all payments in respect of the Assigned 
Interest (including payments of principal, interest, fees and other amounts) to the Assignee whether such 
amounts have accrued prior to or on or after the Effective Date. The Assignor and the Assignee shall make all 
appropriate adjustments in payments by the Administrative Agent for periods prior to the Effective Date or with 
respect to the making of this assignment directly between themselves. 

